## Linux System Administrator
---
### __Commands__

* `uname`:  use this to get system information. the `-a` flag will give kernel and processor info.
* `lsmod`:  this command will list the modules loaded by the kernel. 
* `modprobe`: this command is used to remove or load modules into the kernel. 
* `lspci`: this will list all pci devices on system. Best to run with `-v` command to display more info on devices. The `-k` option will also include the modules that the devices use.
* `lsusb`: this lists the usb devices. 

